This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Digital Libraries (cs.DL) as it discusses bibliographic databases such as Web of Science, Scopus, and Google Scholar that are commonly used in digital libraries. It also covers topics related to information retrieval (cs.IR) such as the selection of publications and citations to be included in the calculation of citation impact indicators. Additionally, the paper touches on topics related to cybersecurity (cs.CY) such as normalization of citation impact indicators and counting methods for dealing with co-authored publications. The paper also discusses citation impact indicators for journals, which could fall under the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) or Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) depending on the context.
